  },
  {
    question: "What heritage permits do I need for waterproofing in Old Oakville?",
    answer: "Properties within Oakville's Heritage Conservation Districts (primarily Old Oakville along Lakeshore Road) require a Heritage Permit for exterior foundation work. The application process through the Town of Oakville's Heritage Planning department typically takes 4-6 weeks and requires detailed plans showing proposed work, materials, and restoration methods. We handle permit coordination as part of our service, providing heritage-compliant drawings and material specifications. Interior waterproofing (drainage systems, sump pumps) generally does NOT require heritage permits since it doesn't affect exterior appearance. For designated heritage properties, we work with the Oakville Heritage Society to ensure all work meets conservation standards."
