  {
    question: "How does Lake Ontario proximity affect Oakville basements?",
    answer: "Lake Ontario's proximity (Oakville's entire southern boundary) creates consistently high water tables, especially in Old Oakville, Bronte, and Lakeshore properties. The lake raises groundwater levels by 1-2 meters compared to inland areas, creating constant hydrostatic pressure against foundations. Lake-effect precipitation adds 50-100mm of additional rainfall annually, and spring lake levels can rise 30-50cm, pushing groundwater inland. We address this with comprehensive exterior waterproofing membranes rated for continuous hydrostatic pressure, high-capacity sump systems (often dual pumps), and deep perimeter drainage below footing level. Lakefront properties may need marine-grade materials and special attention to foundation stability from wave-induced soil movement."
