  {
    question: "When is the best season for waterproofing in Oakville?",
    answer: "Late spring through fall (May-October) is ideal for exterior waterproofing in Oakville — dry soil conditions, warm weather for membrane curing, and minimal frost risk. However, we work year-round with cold-weather protocols for winter emergencies. Spring (April-May) is our busiest season due to snowmelt and rain revealing basement issues, so booking 4-6 weeks ahead is recommended. Summer (June-August) offers the most predictable weather and faster project completion. Fall (September-October) is excellent for pre-winter protection before freeze-thaw cycles begin. Interior drainage systems can be installed any time of year. For urgent leaks or flooding, we provide 90-minute emergency response 24/7/365 regardless of season."
  },
  {
    question: "Can I get Halton Region rebates for waterproofing?",
    answer: "Halton Region periodically offers rebates for basement flooding prevention, including backwater valve installation ($1,250-$1,800 rebate) and sump pump upgrades ($400-$750 rebate). The Halton Healthy Homes program provides subsidies for low-income homeowners for water infiltration solutions. The Town of Oakville occasionally runs stormwater management incentive programs that may include foundation drainage rebates. Ontario Seniors' Home Safety Tax Credit provides up to $2,500 annually for waterproofing for residents 65+. CMHC Green Home grants (up to $5,000) can apply when waterproofing is combined with insulation or energy efficiency work. Rebate availability changes annually — we check current programs during your free inspection and help with applications."
