    question: "How long does basement waterproofing take in Oakville?",
    answer: "Exterior waterproofing in Oakville typically takes 5-7 days for an average home: 1-2 days for excavation, 2-3 days for membrane application and drainage installation, 1-2 days for backfill and yard restoration. Heritage homes in Old Oakville may take 8-10 days due to careful stone foundation work and permit inspections. Large luxury homes in Glen Abbey with complex landscaping can take 10-14 days. Interior drainage systems take 2-4 days with minimal disruption. Weather delays (rain, extreme cold) can add 1-3 days. We work Monday-Saturday with flexible scheduling to minimize impact on your routine. Emergency repairs are often completed within 24-48 hours. Most Oakville projects are finished within two weeks from start to final grading."
